<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri"  FontSize="14">The following is a list of the types of bindings that can be performed in a diagram.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph >
<Bold>Business Object Binding</Bold> - Demonstrates how a collection of business objects can be bound using a directed-tree layout.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph >
<Bold>XML Data Binding</Bold> - Demonstrates how data from the XML data provider can be bound using a directed-tree layout.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph >
<Bold>Diagram Binding With TreeView</Bold> - Demonstrates synchronization of business object between the Diagram Control and TreeView Control.
</Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>
